FBIS4-45570 "jptdd028__l94070" JPRS-TDD-94-028-L JPRS Narcotics 19 June 1994 EAST ASIA JAPAN Police Confiscate 152 Kg of Illegal Stimulants Police Confiscate 152 Kg of Illegal Stimulants OW1906131394 Tokyo KYODO in English 1307 GMT 19 Jun 94 OW1906131394 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Fukuoka, June 19 KYODO -- Police and maritime safety officials on Sunday [19 June] confiscated some 152 kilogram of illegal stimulants, worth about 28 billion yen on the market, from a fishing boat at a port on Amami Oshima Island, Kagoshima Prefecture. Police arrested Takamasa Kurimoto, 41, a local yakuza syndicate leader, and four others on the vessel for allegedly violating a drug control law. Police suspect the involvement of a large-scale smuggling organization.
